content.description: Proceed up a series of ledges that look unlikely to have an easy connecting line to a shallow right facing corner.  Finish using some holds to right and then back left.
content.location: Ungrateful is currently the left most climb on the Leaning Wall [west] side of the Black Dike Walls.

content.description: A somewhat overhanging gully-like emergence of 2 angled faces that may appear more like a crack climb but the somewhat undetectable holds when viewing the route form the ground make for a difficult onsight.
content.location: The route begins at the most obvious overhanging gully on the Overhanging Wall of  the Black Dike Walls and is just right Gordian.

content.description: An overhanging small crimp face just above ground level when properly traversed rightward leads to a more obvious line of holds above.
content.location: 1st route on the left end on east side of the Black Dike wall.

content.description: Some stemming will get you onto the overhanging bulge that has big holds and long reaches. The last portion of the climb crosses into the territory of coin sized holds and is more at arete climbing.
content.location: The rightmost route on Leaner Wall of the west side of the Black Dyke Walls on the leaning corner.

content.description: This route was done before Coins to cross the Stix but has the same great start and moves on the overhanging almost corner like face/bulge but about half way up exits left but not enough to use the large crack for finishing.
content.location: Begins at rightmost route on the west face of the Black Dyke Walls, but leads to easy face holds near the big crack left of the arete of Coins to cross the Stix.
